# Configuration Cache for iron_bessy Console
#
# WHAT IS THIS?
# This file caches build parameters so you don't need to re-enter them every time.
# It's gitignored and auto-generated on first run.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
# - First run: console prompts for every parameter and saves them here
# - Subsequent runs: console restores cached values (shows them as defaults)
# - Use --no-cache flag to re-prompt for everything: ./iron_bessy.sh --no-cache
#
# STRUCTURE:
# - PROXMOX_CLUSTER is always at the top level (no section)
# - Other keys are stored under [CLUSTER_NAME] sections
# - Each cluster maintains independent cached values (e.g., different nodes)
#
# CLEANUP:
# - Delete stale entries manually if resources are removed from Proxmox
# - If console says "not found on node", the value here is out of sync
